  "prompt": "What are the some of the best lines in English songs?",
  "response": "There are countless memorable lines in English songs across various genres. Here are some iconic and impactful lines that have resonated with listeners:\n\n1. **\u201cImagine all the people living life in peace.\u201d**  \n   - *\"Imagine\" by John Lennon*\n\n2. **\u201cI will survive!\u201d**  \n   - *\"I Will Survive\" by Gloria Gaynor*\n\n3. **\u201cYou may say I\u2019m a dreamer, but I\u2019m not the only one.\u201d**  \n   - *\"Imagine\" by John Lennon*\n\n4. **\u201cIs this the real life? Is this just fantasy?\u201d**  \n   - *\"Bohemian Rhapsody\" by Queen*\n\n5. **\u201cEvery little thing she does is magic.\u201d**  \n   - *\"Every Little Thing She Does Is Magic\" by The Police*\n\n6. **\u201cHello, is it me you\u2019re looking for?\u201d**  \n   - *\"Hello\" by Lionel Richie*\n\n7. **\u201cWe're just two lost souls swimming in a fishbowl.\u201d**  \n   - *\"Wish You Were Here\" by Pink Floyd*\n\n8. **\u201cBecause you know I\u2019m all about that bass, \u2019bout that bass, no treble.\u201d**  \n   - *\"All About That Bass\" by Meghan Trainor*\n\n9. **\u201cIt's a beautiful day, don\u2019t let it get away.\u201d**  \n   - *\"Beautiful Day\" by U2*\n\n10. **\u201cI want to hold your hand.\u201d**  \n    - *\"I Want to Hold Your Hand\" by The Beatles*\n\n11. **\u201cYou can go your own way.\u201d**  \n    - *\"Go Your Own Way\" by Fleetwood Mac*\n\n12. **\u201cI\u2019m starting with the man in the mirror.\u201d**  \n    - *\"Man in the Mirror\" by Michael Jackson*\n\nThese lines capture a range of emotions and themes, including love, hope, resilience, and self-reflection, making them timeless and powerful in the world of music.",
